# Project Structure

## Directory layout

```
project-root/
├── index.html
├── vite.config.js
├── eslint.config.js
├── package.json
└── src/
    ├── main.jsx          # Entry point — mounts router
    ├── App.jsx           # Root layout component
    ├── routes.jsx        # Route definitions array
    ├── utils.jsx         # Shared utility functions
    ├── index.css         # Global styles (Tailwind import)
    └── components/       # All page and UI components
        ├── Navbar.jsx
        ├── ErrorPage.jsx
        └── ...
```

## File naming

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| React components | PascalCase `.jsx` | `LoginPage.jsx`, `Navbar.jsx` |
| Utilities / config | camelCase `.jsx` or `.js` | `utils.jsx`, `routes.jsx` |
| CSS | kebab-case `.css` | `index.css` |
| Build configs | kebab-case `.js` | `vite.config.js` |

## Key conventions

- Use `.jsx` for all React files (no TypeScript)
- `src/components/` holds all page-level and shared UI components
- Utility functions shared across components live in `src/utils.jsx`
- Route config lives in `src/routes.jsx`, imported once in `main.jsx`
- `src/App.jsx` is the root layout only — it renders `<Navbar>` and `<Outlet>`, manages global auth state
- Keep `src/` flat except for the `components/` subdirectory
